ce:section.ce:para:
One issue that arises when integrating the FE model and the present version of the EFFT model is that the strain and/or stress boundary conditions in the EFFT model correspond to the average strain and/or stress applied to the periodized unit cell. Another drawback of the EFFT model in its present application is the requirement for periodic boundary conditions across unit cell boundaries. This led to artefact stresses at some boundary areas where spurious discontinuities in the microstructure occurred (Fig. 6). These artefacts had a notable effect on the available work in only a few regions (
Fig. 9
). Here analysis of a larger region including a buffer zone of the same material could be attempted to minimize the effect of the artefact stresses in the region of interest.
